column1: #Software_Description: ChrTracer3 software was developed for analysis of raw DNA labeled images. As an input
column2: it takes an.xlsx table containing information and folder names of the DNA experiment. As an output
column3: it returns tab delimited.txt Þles with drift-corrected x
column5: z positions for all labeled barcodes. These can be used directly to calculate the nm scale distances between all pairs of labeled loci. The current version of the software as of this writing is ChrTracer3.
